DaVita, meanwhile, runs or provides administrative services at nearly 1,600 dialysis facilities, serving about 124,000 patients. "This acquisition introduces us to several new geographies and makes us a more effective competitor in selected areas," said DaVita Chairman and Chief Executive Kent Thiry.
